      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub in the butter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan. Whisk the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{sea-salt-fine}} and {{caster-sugar}} in a wide bowl. Rub the {{unsalted-butter}} in with cold fingertips until the mixture looks like coarse breadcrumbs with pea-sized pieces of butter still visible. The bigger pieces give the flakiness.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fold and turn",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour in the {{buttermilk}} and stir with a fork until the dough comes together; it will look rough. Tip onto a floured surface and pat to a rectangle about 2 cm thick. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Fold the dough into thirds",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99a7y100009wv4uq7ur0zi"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " like a letter, turn ninety degrees, and pat back to a 2 cm slab. Repeat the fold once more. Cut twelve rounds with a floured 5 cm cutter, straight down.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 12 to 14 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set on a lined baking tray with 3 cm between scones. Brush with the beaten {{eggs}}. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes; the tops should be golden and the sides should show layered flakes. Cool on a rack 5 minutes before splitting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
